<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - REMOVAL AND INSTALLATION - Modular Door Hardware Assembly</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1603816" svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Modular Door Hardware Assembly</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Removal procedures show driver side; passenger side procedures are the same.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Modular door hardware procedures are the same for either front or rear cab doors.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>The modular door hardware assembly consists of the window regulator assembly, front
                                and rear window run channels, inner and outer door handles, and door latch. This
                                assembly is installed and removed as a module.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Lower cab door glass to the bottom before removing trim panel.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara></specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove door trim panel. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603812.xml" xrefid="x1603812">
                        <emph type="bold">DOOR TRIM PANEL</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603812"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove door vapor barrier. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603813.xml" xrefid="x1603813">
                        <emph type="bold">DOOR VAPOR BARRIER</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603813"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove door glass. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603814.xml" xrefid="x1603814">
                        <emph type="bold">DOOR GLASS</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603814"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1603866" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603866.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 84. Door Handle Trim Bezel</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CAB DOOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TRIM BEZEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. OUTER DOOR HANDLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a flat-blade screwdriver covered with a cloth rag to protect the paint, carefully
                    pry door handle trim bezel away from cab door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The plastic tabs on the door handle trim bezel will likely break off during removal. Replace
                        trim bezel if tabs get broken.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four screws securing outer door handle.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1603867" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603867.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 85. Modular Door Hardware Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ASSEMBLY MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNTING GUIDE PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. REGULATOR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. DOOR LATCH BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. MODULAR DOOR HARDWARE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove three door latch bolts securing door latch assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four assembly mounting bolts securing modular door hardware assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove mounting guide pin.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide modular door hardware assembly to the right, lift upward, and pull outward to
                    expose electrical connectors.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1603868" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603868.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 86. Electrical Connectors</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. PUSH-IN FASTENERS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WINDOW MOTOR ELECTRICAL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WINDOW ELECTRIC MOTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. WINDOW RUN CHANNELS</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. DOOR LATCH ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. DOOR LATCH ELECTRICAL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect window motor electrical connector from the electric window motor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove all push-in fasteners securing the wiring harness.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect door latch electrical connector from the door latch assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove modular door hardware assembly.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Installation procedures show driver side; passenger side procedures are the same.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Modular door hardware procedures are the same for either front or rear cab doors.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>The modular door hardware assembly consists of the window regulator assembly, front
                                and rear window run channels, inner and outer door handles, and door latch. This
                                assembly is installed and removed as a module.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position modular door hardware assembly near the cab door and connect the door latch
                    electrical connector to the door latch assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603868">Figure 86, Items 5 and 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install all wiring harness push-in fasteners (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603868">Figure 86, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect window motor electrical connector to window electric motor (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603868">Figure 86, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Guide the top of the window run channels up inside cab door and align door latch
                    assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603868">Figure 86, Items 4 and 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align modular door hardware assembly and install mounting guide pin (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603867">Figure 85, Items 2 and 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install modular door hardware assembly with four assembly mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603867">Figure 85, Items 1 and 5</hotlnk>). Finger tighten bolts only.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Once all four bolts are in place, tighten the bolts to 8 to 10 Lbf-ft (11 to 14 N&#8226;m).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door latch assembly with three door latch bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603867">Figure 85</hotlnk>). Tighten bolts to 8 to 10 Lbf-ft (11 to 14 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install outer door handle with four screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603866">Figure 84, Items 2 and 4</hotlnk>). Tighten screws to 35 to 44 Lbf-in. (4
                    to 5 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>A new outer door handle trim bezel will need to be installed if the plastic tabs were broken
                        off during removal.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install trim bezel and carefully push it in place (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603866">Figure 84, Item 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Ensure the door lock, inner and outer door handles, and door latch assembly are all
                    working properly before proceeding.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door glass. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603814.xml" xrefid="x1603814">
                        <emph type="bold">DOOR GLASS</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603814"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door vapor barrier. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603813.xml" xrefid="x1603813">
                        <emph type="bold">DOOR VAPOR BARRIER</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603813"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door trim panel. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603812.xml" xrefid="x1603812">
                        <emph type="bold">DOOR TRIM PANEL</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603812"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
